## PARTE 3 — FLUXO DE COMUNICAÇÃO E CONTRATOS

### 3.1 Diagrama de Sequência — Fluxo Principal de um Round

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant DE as DebateEngine
    participant CA as CriticAgent
    participant PA as ProponentAgent
    participant DST as DebateStateTracker
    participant VB as ValidationBoard
    participant DISK as .forge/validation_board.json

    DE->>CA: review_artifact(artifact, context)
    CA-->>DE: critique_text (string bruta)

    DE->>DST: extract_issues_from_critique(critique_text, round_num, board)
    DST->>DST: _parse_level1(critique_text) → IssueRecords
    alt Nível 1 falhou (0 matches)
        DST->>DST: _parse_level2(critique_text) → IssueRecords
        alt Nível 2 falhou
            DST->>DST: _parse_level3(critique_text) → IssueRecords
        end
    end
    DST->>DST: _deduplicate(records, board)
    loop Para cada IssueRecord novo
        DST->>VB: add_issue(record)
        VB->>VB: _validate_no_duplicate(record)
        VB-->>DST: ok
    end
    DST-->>DE: ["ISS-01", "ISS-02"] (IDs registrados)

    DE->>DST: extract_decisions_from_text(critique_text, round_num, board)
    DST->>VB: add_decision(DecisionRecord)
    VB-->>DST: ok
    DST-->>DE: ["D-01"]

    DE->>PA: defend_artifact(artifact, critique, context)
    PA-->>DE: defense_text (string bruta)

    DE->>DST: extract_resolutions_from_defense(defense_text, round_num, board)
    DST->>DST: _extract_accepted_block(defense_text)
    loop Para cada issue OPEN no Board
        DST->>DST: _match_resolution(issue, accepted_block)
        alt Match encontrado
            DST->>VB: resolve_issue(issue_id, round_num, resolution)
            VB->>VB: _validate_transition(OPEN → RESOLVED)
            VB-->>DST: ok
        end
    end
    DST-->>DE: ["ISS-01"] (IDs resolvidos)

    DE->>VB: persist(".forge/validation_board.json")
    VB->>VB: snapshot()
    VB->>DISK: json.dump(snapshot, sort_keys=True)
    DISK-->>VB: ok
    VB-->>DE: None
```

### 3.2 Diagrama de Estado — ValidationBoard (IssueRecord)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> OPEN : add_issue(IssueRecord)

    OPEN --> RESOLVED : resolve_issue(issue_id, round_num, resolution)\n[resolution != ""]
    OPEN --> DEFERRED : defer_issue(issue_id, round_num)

    RESOLVED --> [*] : estado terminal (sucesso)
    DEFERRED --> [*] : estado terminal (postergado)

    OPEN --> ERROR_DUPLICATE : add_issue com mesmo ID\n→ ignorado silenciosamente
    RESOLVED --> InvalidStateTransitionError : qualquer transição\n→ exceção levantada
    DEFERRED --> InvalidStateTransitionError : qualquer transição\n→ exceção levantada
```

### 3.3 Diagrama de Estado — ValidationBoard (DecisionRecord)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> PROPOSED : add_decision(DecisionRecord)

    PROPOSED --> VALIDATED : validate_decision(decision_id, round_num, evidence)\n[evidence != ""]
    PROPOSED --> CONTESTED : contest_decision(decision_id, round_num)

    VALIDATED --> [*] : estado terminal (consenso)
    CONTESTED --> [*] : estado terminal (sem consenso)

    VALIDATED --> InvalidStateTransitionError : qualquer transição
    CONTESTED --> InvalidStateTransitionError : qualquer transição
```

### 3.4 Diagrama de Estado — ValidationBoard (AssumptionRecord)

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> UNTESTED : add_assumption(AssumptionRecord)\n[via register_assumptions_from_text]

    UNTESTED --> VALIDATED : validate_assumption(assumption_id, round_num, evidence)
    UNTESTED --> FLAGGED : flag_assumption(assumption_id, round_num)

    VALIDATED --> [*] : estado terminal (confirmado)
    FLAGGED --> [*] : estado terminal (risco identificado)

    VALIDATED --> InvalidStateTransitionError : qualquer transição
    FLAGGED --> InvalidStateTransitionError : qualquer transição
```

### 3.5 Tabela de Transições de Estado

| Tipo | Estado Atual | Evento | Estado Novo | Condição | Ação |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Issue | OPEN | `resolve_issue` | RESOLVED | `resolution != ""` | Setar `round_resolved`, `resolution` |
| Issue | OPEN | `defer_issue` | DEFERRED | sempre | Setar `round_resolved` |
| Issue | OPEN | `add_issue` (mesmo ID) | OPEN | ID já existe | Ignorar silenciosamente |
| Issue | RESOLVED | qualquer | — | — | Levantar `InvalidStateTransitionError` |
| Issue | DEFERRED | qualquer | — | — | Levantar `InvalidStateTransitionError` |
| Decision | PROPOSED | `validate_decision` | VALIDATED | `evidence != ""` | Setar `round_resolved`, `evidence` |
| Decision | PROPOSED | `contest_decision` | CONTESTED | sempre | Setar `round_resolved` |
| Decision | VALIDATED | qualquer | — | — | Levantar `InvalidStateTransitionError` |
| Decision | CONTESTED | qualquer | — | — | Levantar `InvalidStateTransitionError` |
| Assumption | UNTESTED | `validate_assumption` | VALIDATED | `evidence != ""` | Setar `round_resolved`, `evidence` |
| Assumption | UNTESTED | `flag_assumption` | FLAGGED | sempre | Setar `round_resolved` |
| Assumption | VALIDATED | qualquer | — | — | Levantar `InvalidStateTransitionError` |
| Assumption | FLAGGED | qualquer | — | — | Levantar `InvalidStateTransitionError` |

### 3.6 Contrato de Erro

```python
class InvalidStateTransitionError(Exception):
    """
    Levantada quando ValidationBoard recebe transição de estado inválida.
    
    Atributos:
        record_id: str   — ID do registro (ex: "ISS-01")
        current:   str   — estado atual (ex: "RESOLVED")
        attempted: str   — transição tentada (ex: "resolve_issue")
    """
    def __init__(self, record_id: str, current: str, attempted: str):
        self.record_id = record_id
        self.current = current
        self.attempted = attempted
        super().__init__(
            f"[{record_id}] Transição inválida: '{attempted}' "
            f"a partir do estado '{current}'"
        )
```

